l actions (FACS), and event-related brain potentials (ERP) of normed minimal quadruplets with frightening and humorous incongruities as well as (in)coherent stimuli. The results suggest that humor and horror share cognitive resources to detect and resolve incongruities. To better distinguish humor from neighboring phenomena, this book refines current humor theories by incorporating humor and horror in a cognitive incongruity processing model.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aEmotive (Linguistics). 0aHorror. 0aWit and humor. 4aHorror. 4aHumor. 4aInkongruenz. 70(DE-588)106428129X0(DE-627)8131239250(DE-576)42387604XaInkongruenz2gnd 70(DE-588)4026170-00(DE-627)1062893730(DE-576)208965289aHumor2gnd 70(DE-588)4201995-30(DE-627)1051618020(DE-576)210145587aHorror2gnd 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aHorror.  aHumor.  aIncongruity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMouton eBook Package 2022z97831107912970 cEPUBz97831107648020 cprintz978311076468040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076474140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110764741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110764741/original  a978-3-11-079129-7  Mouton eBook Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK